Subject: Annual Report Request

Good morning Youth-Nex colleagues,

=20

Per the announcement below in our last update email, if you are receiving t=
his email, we would like to include you in our annual report! This is a year=
ly summary document we provide to our funders/supporters, and use for develo=
pment/advancement purposes that highlights members of our community and thei=
r accomplishments. Please reply with your current CV or updated accomplishme=
nts/scholarship from July 2024 to now!=20

=20

We are hoping to connect with scholars now before graduation that may be of=
fline this summer. Thank you for supporting this annual report effort!

=20

=20

From: Youth-Nex <youth-nex@virginia.edu>
Date: Friday, April 18, 2025 at 7:00=E2=80=AFAM
To: "yn-ehd@virginia.edu" <yn-ehd@virginia.edu>, "yn-uva@virginia.edu" <yn-=
uva@virginia.edu>, "YN-Gradstudents@virginia.edu" <YN-Gradstudents@virginia.=
edu>, "YN-Affiliate@virginia.edu" <YN-Affiliate@virginia.edu>
Subject: YN Apr25 update | New Collaboration Corner, Annual Report, etc.

=20

Dear Youth-Nex colleagues,

=20

As we approach the spring semester finals, this update email is for interna=
l members of our Youth-Nex community with community updates, and more! If yo=
u need any assistance or support, please do not hesitate to reach out to any=
 of the Youth-Nex staff.

=20

ANNOUNCEMENTS
NEW: Introducing the Youth-Nex Collaboration Corner! The "Collaboration Cor=
ner" is a fresh addition to our monthly or quarterly internal update emails =
to highlight opportunities for collaboration, which will live under UVA netb=
adge on the Youth-Nex Drive. This effort is designed to shine a spotlight on=
 our diverse scholars, their innovative projects, and the groundbreaking wor=
k being done across Youth-Nex (see attached PDF for more on this new effort)=
. Watch for updates and contact Leslie if you are interested in being featur=
ed!
YN Annual Report: If you are receiving this email, we would like to include=
 you in our annual report! This is a yearly summary document we provide to o=
ur funders/supporters, and use for development purposes that highlights memb=
ers of our community. Please reply with your current CV or updated accomplis=
hment/scholarships from since July 2024! We are hoping to connect with schol=
ars now that may not be online this summer.=20
Summer Wage Planning: The upcoming UVA summer HR period will run from 5/19/=
2025 through 8/10/25! We are starting to plan for your summer wage needs so =
they can be shepherded through the new hiring requirements. Please let Lesli=
e know what extension or new hires you have, and watch for communications!
Faculty members are sometimes targeted, on social media and elsewhere, for =
the research they conduct or the views they express. The UVA Provost's Onlin=
e Targeting Response Resources provides guidance and support for navigating =
online harassment.
Youth Writing Opportunity: Attached is a call for proposals for upcoming sp=
ecial issue of English Journal focused on student/youth voice, research, and=
 activism. They are welcoming manuscripts written solely by young folks or c=
o-authored with teachers/mentors due 8/1/25. Email Lauren Leigh Kelly at lau=
ren.kelly@gse.rutgers.edu with questions!
Ethical Approaches to Mandatory Reporting Study: Please see the attached re=
cruitment flyer from a former YN student who is conducting a qualitative stu=
dy on researchers who work with youth and families, and handle situations in=
volving mandatory reporting (see interest form).
Happy upcoming birthdays to Martha Pullen (5/6) and Taina Quiles (5/9)! You=
 are welcome and encouraged to share your birthday in this survey to be reco=
gnized in the future!
=20

REMINDERS
YN Student Interest Database for Volunteers: As a reminder, every month we =
are adding new students (UVA and non-UVA) who are interested in working with=
 members of the center. With these uncertain budget times, please note that =
some students are looking to volunteer this summer if you are looking for su=
pport!
As we approach more conferences before graduation (AERA/SRCD, etc.), please=
 consider re-reviewing our Youth-Nex Job Market Candidates to mention to you=
r colleagues or introduce this junior scholars, where applicable!
YN Core Faculty:=20
Please let Crystal know of any potential proposals you plan on submitting b=
etween now and end of July. Even if they don=E2=80=99t come to fruition, it helps =
to know about them so that we can plan accordingly and ensure adequate cover=
age between Youth-Nex and the EHD pre-award office.=20
Given the recent email updates from President Ryan and Dean Rowley regardin=
g budget challenges and discretionary expenditures, please read over the EHD=
 memos carefully. Please note that YN has also suspended non-essential expen=
ditures on non-sponsored funds including Youth-Nex specific professional dev=
elopment support, and is requiring documented PI approval for all travel. Pl=
ease follow-up with Crystal/Martha with questions!
If you missed it, attached here is an end-of-the-year message from YN Direc=
tor Nancy Deutsch!
=20

EVENTS
Upcoming! Sp25 Research Talk: On Friday May 2nd at 11 AM in Ridley 302, You=
th-Nex is hosting Dr. Daniel J. Flannery on "Challenges to Positive Youth De=
velopment: Violence & Mental Health in Everyday Life=E2=80=9D (iCal is attached). =
There is a hybrid option for designated remote employees or non-local partne=
rs, and options for on-Grounds parking is available for non-UVA local partne=
rs who may want to attend (please reach out to Leslie for more info).
Fall Talk Save the Date: We will be welcoming Dr. Deborah Rivas-Drake (Step=
hanie J. Rowley Collegiate Professor, and Associate Dean for Diversity, Incl=
usion, Justice, and Equity in the Marsal School of Education at University o=
f Michigan) on Friday 9/26. Please mark your calendar now and watch for futu=
re updates!
=20

NEWS
Goal Setting with Middle Schoolers: Post-doc Jia Ma shares tips and downloa=
dable resources for helping students set goals.
Social Media & Mental Health: Teen author Reanna summarizes and reflects on=
 a debate at our fall conference.=20
EHD Podcast: Check out and listen to Dr. Lora Henderson Smith and her schol=
arship being highlighted in this new episode!
AERA Fellow: Congrats to Dr. Catherine Bradshaw who was selected as a 2025 =
AERA Fellow!
Science of Parenting: The UVA Magazine highlights work by our Dr.s Wintre F=
oxworth Johnson and Amrisha Vaish.
=20

For more updates on news at Youth-Nex this month, please follow us on any o=
f the social media platforms! Thank you for supporting Youth-Nex and the imp=
ortant work happening here.

 =20

=20

--

